34#include "krb5_locl.h"
35#include "ccache_plugin.h"
36#ifdef HAVE_DLFCN_H
37#include <dlfcn.h>
38#endif
39#include <assert.h>
40
41/*
42 * cc_plugin_register_to_context is executed once per krb5_init_context().
43 * Its job is to register the plugin's krb5_cc_ops structure with the
44 * krb5_context.
45 */
46
47static krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
48cc_plugin_register_to_context(krb5_context context, const void *plug, void *plugctx, void *userctx)
49{
50 krb5_cc_ops *ccops = (krb5_cc_ops *)plugctx;
51 krb5_error_code ret;
52
53 if (ccops == NULL || ccops->version < KRB5_CC_OPS_VERSION)
54 return KRB5_PLUGIN_NO_HANDLE;
55
56 ret = krb5_cc_register(context, ccops, TRUE);
57 if (ret != 0)
58 *((krb5_error_code *)userctx) = ret;
59
60 return KRB5_PLUGIN_NO_HANDLE;
61}
62
63KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
64_krb5_load_ccache_plugins(krb5_context context)
65{
66 krb5_error_code userctx = 0;
67
68 (void)_krb5_plugin_run_f(context, "krb5", KRB5_PLUGIN_CCACHE,
69 0, 0, &userctx, cc_plugin_register_to_context);
70
71 return userctx;
72}
